HEADWORD: Pyromorphite
<hw>Pyr`o*mor"phite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[G.
<ets>pyromorphit</ets>, from Gr. <?/ fire + <grk>morfh`</grk>
form.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>Native lead phosphate with lead
chloride, occurring in bright green and brown hexagonal crystals and
also massive; -- so called because a fused globule crystallizes in
cooling.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pyromorphous</ent>⟦br⟧
